Project Apparel Price Optimization¶

Objective: The main idea behind this problem is the following question: As manager of a company/store, how much should I charge in order to maximize my revenue or profit? Obviously, the answer isn’t as high as possible. If you charge one hundred dollars, probably only one or two people will accept to buy it. Although the profit per product is very high, you probably won’t even your fixed costs. Charge a very small is also not the best call.

Let's start

Ridge regression¶

We will now take a look at scikitlearn's API implimenting Ridge regression, remember that the cost function to be minimised while implimenting ridge regression is 𝑅𝑆𝑆(𝛽)+𝐶(𝛽)=𝑅𝑆𝑆(𝛽)+𝜆(Σ𝛽2𝑖), 𝜆 is represented by 𝛼 in scikitlearn's api

ElasticNet¶

Scikitlearn impliments a hybrid regularization scheme called "elastic net", the cost function in this case is 𝑅𝑆𝑆(𝛽)+𝜆𝐿1𝑅𝑎𝑡𝑖𝑜∑|𝛽𝑖|+𝜆(1−𝐿1𝑅𝑎𝑡𝑖𝑜)∑𝛽2𝑖
